  m_Name: Pes_Proximal_Phalanx_D3_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Proximal_Phalanx_D3_L
  partName: Pes Proximal Phalanx D3 Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left proximal phalanx of the third hind digit is located between the metatarsal
    and middle phalanx within the canine hindpaw. This bone supports coordinated
    toe movement and contributes to balanced weight distribution during locomotion.
    Tendons and ligaments attached to the proximal phalanx enable controlled flexion
    and extension while
  - stabilizing the digit during movement. The third digit plays an important role
    in traction, balance, and propulsion during walking and running activities. Proper
    structural integrity is necessary for smooth hindpaw mechanics and coordinated
    gait patterns. Injury or abnormalities affecting this phalanx may impair movement
    efficiency and reduce overall hindlimb stability significantly.
